# Team Operating Principles

This project is built by a solo developer (the CEO) using AI agent personas. Optimize for:

## Speed Over Perfection
- Ship working code fast, iterate based on real usage
- Don't over-engineer for scale you don't have yet
- Prefer simple solutions that work today over elegant solutions that take a week

## Communication Through Memory
- All agents maintain memory files in `.cursor/memory/`
- Cross-team decisions go in `shared-context.md`
- Never make an assumption about another agent's domain — check shared-context first
- If information is missing, flag it as an open question rather than guessing

## One User, Fast Iteration
- The app has one user right now — the CEO
- Optimize for developer velocity, not enterprise patterns
- Skip RBAC, multi-tenancy, and horizontal scaling until they're actually needed
- Auth can start simple (single user) and evolve

## Code Standards
- TypeScript everywhere (frontend and backend)
- Explicit types over `any`
- Small, focused files — if a file exceeds ~200 lines, it probably needs splitting
- Meaningful names — code should read like prose
- Comments for "why", not "what"
